 Change Debate makes a powerful case for a more scientifically literate public, a more socially engaged scientific community, and a more thoughtful mode of public discourse.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aClimatic changeszUnited StatesxPublic opinion. 0aPolitical culturezUnited States. 0aPublic opinionzUnited States. 0aSciencezUnited StatesxPublic opinion. 0aSocial psychologyzUnited States. 4aClimate Change. 4aClimate Contrarians. 4aCulture. 4aDecision-Making. 4aPsychology. 4aSociology. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Green Business.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311070398640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080479505040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804795050423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804795050.jpg  a978-3-11-070398-6  SUP Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles